Title: BRS symmetry from renormalization group flow

Authors: M. Bonini, M. D'Attanasio and G. Marchesini

Comments: 9 pages, LaTex, to be published in Phys. Lett. B

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B346 (1995) 87-93

By using the exact renormalization group formulation we prove perturbativelythe Slavnov-Taylor (ST) identities in SU(2) Yang-Mills theory. This resultslocal part is valid; {\it solvability}, i.e. the local part of ST identities isvalid if the couplings of the effective action with non-negative dimensions areproperly chosen.